==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parasitical
<hw>Par`a*sit"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(p⟦acr⟧r`⟦adot⟧*s⟦icr⟧t"⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>parasiticus</ets>, Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>parasitique</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of the nature of a parasite; having the habits of a
parasite; fawning for food or favors; sycophantic.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Parasitic</xex> preachers.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> leechlike, bloodsucking.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to
parasites; living on, or deriving nourishment from, some other living
animal or plant. See <er>Parasite</er>, 2 & 3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Parasitic gull</b></col>, <col><b>Parasitic
jager</b></col></mcol>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Jager</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Par`a*sit"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Par`a*sit"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>parasiticidal</ent>⟦br⟧
